      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:40:8",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/40/756",
      "text": [
        " «يُصَلِّي فِيهِمَا جَمِيعاً."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.756 - Safwan ibn Yahya wrote to Abu Al-Hasan, Imam Musa ibn Jafar Al-Kadhim (as) asking about a man who has two garments, one of which has been contaminated with urine, but he does not know which one. When the time for prayer arrives and he fears missing it, and he has no water available, what should he do?\nImam (as) said: \"He should pray in both of them.\""
        ]
      }
    },
